         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot. &amp; zool Garden ¶ 16 Aug 1859 ¶ My dear Mr LaTrobe ¶  ¶ Since your departure from us I bore always your request in mind, of furnishing you with a specimen of the genus Latrobea, establish...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">59.08.16</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Charles La Trobe</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">Archives de l'Etat de Neuchâtel, fonds Petitpierre/La Trobe, dossier 17/24</seg>
               <seg style="">,</seg> Neuchâtel, Switzerland.<seg style="font-size: 9pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Transcribed from copy held by the State Library of Victoria, MS 13354, Box 3, Folder 30.</p>
               </note>Melbourne bot. &amp; zool Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">16 Aug 1859</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Mr LaTrobe</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Since your departure from us I bore always your request in mind, of furnishing you with a specimen of the genus Latrobea, established by Prof. Meisner, but was not able to do so until now, when our collector sends for the first time the <name key="Latrobea%20genistoides">Latrobea genistoides</name> from W. Australia. I feel confident, altho' I have seen no specimens of it, that the <name key="Latrobea%20Brunonis">Latrobea Brunonis</name> Meisner is nothing but a meagre desert form of L. genistoides<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation: 'The letter to be returned with the annexed discription of the genus.'</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My work on the plants of Victoria, which you, much beloved Sir, so kindfully &amp; generously initiated, is now under the press and many beautiful illustrations for it are prepared. My multifarious duties do not render it possible to make much rapid progress with it, yet I hope, si fata velint<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">if the fates allow.</p>
               </note> —, to send you the first fascicle before the end of the year.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M's hopes were not realised; the work was not published until March 1862 (see B62.03.03).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Our mutual venerable friend, Sir William Hooker, takes in my labours as lively an interest as ever.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wishing with your numerous friends here you all prosperity I remain, dear &amp; esteemed Sir, your always</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">grateful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">C. J. Latrobe Esq. C.B.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <name key="Latrobea%20Brunonis">Latrobea Brunonis</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Latrobea%20genistoides">Latrobea genistoides</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
